    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Animal models are essential for understanding the pathogenesis of SARS-CoV-2 and for developing therapeutic strategies. Replicon delivery particles (RDPs) were a component of trans-complementary systems for SARS-CoV-2, which is a safe and convenient tool in researching SARS-CoV-2 in animal biosafety level-II laboratory (ABSL-2). Here, we constructed a mouse model that conditional expressing SARS-CoV-2 N on the background of the K18-hACE2 KI mice. The SARS-CoV-2 N with flanked loxP-stop-loxP sequence was under the CAG promoter, and this cassette was knocked into the Tiger locus of mouse by CRISPR-Cas9 (K18-hACE2-N KI). By mating K18-hACE2-N KI mice with Cre tool mice, the offspring can express SARS-CoV-2 N (Cre-N-hACE2 KI) systemically and in a tissue-specific manner. Cre-N-hACE2 KI exhibited susceptibility to the SARS-CoV-2 \u0394N-GFP/HBiT infection. The viral loads in lung exhibited a mountain-like trend, peaking at 4 days post-infection, and lung injuries can be observed. Overall, we demonstrated a mouse model infection for SARS-CoV-2 \u0394N-GFP/HBiT to understand SARS-CoV-2 pathogenesis.</jats:p>",
